The paper deals with lossy source compression, which is a topic in information theory (cs.IT). The soft-covering lemma is a key tool used in the analysis, which is also commonly used in coding theory (cs.CC). The paper also examines the multi-terminal source coding problem, which is a topic in distributed systems (cs.DS). The non-asymptotic analysis used in the point-to-point case is related to statistical learning theory (cs.LG). Finally, the paper discusses the properties of random binning, which is a technique used in information theory and communication systems (cs.SI).
